{
  "id": "card_n_9d43ee4dac10",
  "kind": "note",
  "title": "Easton: Og",
  "body": "Gigantic, the king of Bashan, who was defeated by Moses in a pitched battle at Edrei, and was slain along with his sons (Deut. 1:4), and whose kingdom was given to the tribes of Reuben and Gad and half the tribe of Manasseh (Num. 21:32-35; Deut. 3:1-13). His bedstead (or rather sarcophagus) was of iron (or ironstone), 9 cubits in length and 4 cubits in breadth. His overthrow was afterwards celebrated in song (Ps. 135:11; 136:20). (See SIHON.)",
  "source": {
    "label": "Matthew Easton, Illustrated Bible Dictionary (1897)",
